## ğŸ› Troubleshooting

**Quick Diagnosis:** Run `aii doctor` to check your setup automatically.

| Issue | Solution |
|-------|----------|
| âŒ `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY not found` | Run `aii config init` or `export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="key"` |
| âŒ `aii command not found` | Restart terminal or check PATH: `uv tool install aiiware-cli` |
| âš ï¸ Slow responses | Check network or try different provider: `aii config init` |
| ğŸ” Need diagnostics | Run `aii doctor` or enable debug: `AII_DEBUG=1 aii your-command` |
| ğŸ”„ LLM timeout errors | Retry logic automatic in v0.4.1, check `aii doctor` for connectivity |
| âš ï¸ Web search not working | Configure Brave Search API key (optional, free DuckDuckGo fallback available) |
| ğŸ™ GitHub operations failing | **v0.4.9**: Use `aii mcp install github` then set `GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN` env var |
| ğŸ” GitHub search returns 0 results | **FIXED in v0.4.8 (Oct 9)** - Now returns actual repositories! |
| ğŸ”— MCP tools not found | **v0.4.9**: Run `aii mcp catalog` to browse available servers, `aii mcp list` to see installed |
| âš ï¸ MCP token usage shows 0 | **FIXED in v0.4.9** - Token tracking now accurate for all MCP operations |
| ğŸ› Natural language MCP queries show no output | **FIXED in v0.4.9** - Results now display correctly |
| ğŸ“Š Duplicate status lines in output | **FIXED in v0.4.9** - Clean single-line status display |
| ğŸ¥ MCP server not responding | **v0.4.11**: Run `aii mcp status` to check health, automatic retry enabled |
| ğŸ”„ Asyncio shutdown errors | **FIXED in v0.4.11** - Clean shutdown with proper connection cleanup |

